Description: SuddenValues provides web-based services for consumers, merchants, and manufacturers to connect with each other.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: SuddenValues is a company that connects consumers, merchants and manufactures in commerce via its web-based services. They are: SuddenValues Direct is a group sourcing service that enables our customers to consolidate their buying power to get great deals directly from manufacturers. Each week our buyers negotiate deals with manufactures all over the world based on buyer participation. Orders are then collected from SuddenValues subscribers for one week in an effort to meet the minimum order quantity. (We meet it over 95% of the time.) Once the minimum is met, the product is ordered and shipped either directly from the manufacture or from our distribution center. In the rare occasion the minimum is not met, customers are refunded immediately. On average the process from order to delivery takes four weeks. SuddenBlitz is a daily deal services that enables merchants to create and promote a special offer to SuddenValues subscribers in one or more of 1200 plus U.S. communities. The offer, sold to subscribers in the form of a voucher, is promoted to SuddenValues subscribers on its website and via email updates. There is no upfront cost for merchants to participate or restrictions on quantity that must be sold or when an offer can be run. Our only requirement is that a deal must be 50% off or greater; a threshold research has shown required to get consideration from a new customer. To get started creating a SuddenBlitz offer, Merchants can go to http://www.suddenvalues.com and click on the Post Your Deal button in the upper right hand corner of the website. Once setup, the offer is approved by customer service staff and then promoted to SuddenValues subscribers. Merchants receive a generous revenue split (70%) and thanks to a teaming up with PayPal in January 2013—realtime payment. Merchants simply connect their PayPal business account to their promotion and get paid as consumers purchase the offer. The PayPal business account is free and only requires an email verification to get started. SuddenValues is a service that allows local, regional and national merchants to connect with consumers. The service enables merchants to create and manage a website, email, coupons, customer signups and send permission-based email alerts. This includes being able to promote coupons, offers and expanding one’s following via the SuddenValues.com website and services. SuddenValues is a monthly service, with pricing starting at $99 and up, depending on a merchants service requirements. There are additional fees for initial and on-going website development.

Description: Shocking Technologies manufactures Voltage Switchable Dielectric (VSD) materials.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Shocking Technologies, Inc. started operations as a privately held, venture-backed company developing Voltage Switchable Dielectricâ„¢ (VSDâ„¢) materials. A VSDâ„¢ material is a polymer nano-composite that behaves like an insulator (dielectric) during normal circuit operation and becomes conductive when the voltage across the VSDâ„¢ material increases beyond a predefined threshold voltage. The voltage switches back to an insulator again after the voltage drops below the threshold. This unique property, coupled with the ability to tailor the response of the material, opens up several new areas in electronics. The first application being introduced enables embedded electrostatic discharge (ESD) protection in printed circuit boards (PCBs) and semiconductor packages. Subsequent applications will usher in new manufacturing processes as well as novel product designs.

Description: A private equity firm focused on making equity investments in middle-market companies.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Lakewood Capital was formed in 2007 to team with operating management to make control investments in private companies active in the lower middle market. Lakewood targets businesses that have developed a strong position in their core markets and are facing opportunities/challenges/transition as they move toward the next stage of their developments. Lower middle market businesses often reach a point where their existing resources, be they financial, operational or human, need to be expanded, adjusted and/or reallocated to continue to prosper. These times often occur when founding management seeks less active involvement, new market opportunities arise, growth outstrips current capacity, and/or the competitive landscape changes. Lakewood prides itself on partnering with existing management to capitalize on these times of transition, with the mutual goal of building stronger, more dynamic, more competitive operations in the process. As such, we will not be focused on any particular industry but will look for opportunities where we have the ability to work with management, collectively, drawing on resources and experiences each party has developed over many years. Our strategic influence coupled with management’s operational expertise, brought together in a collaborative environment, has served us extremely well over the years, and we believe it will be even more critical over the next several years as the private equity market matures.
